About



Research Interests




Dr. Zhang’s research interests include computer architecture, parallel and distributed systems, and architectural support for system security. He received his BS and MS degrees in Computer Science from Huazhong University of Science of Technology, China, in 1991 and 1994, respectively, and the PhD degree in Computer Science from the College of William and Mary in 2002. He is a member of the IEEE and a senior member of the ACM.







Education

     Ph.D. Computer Science College of William and Mary, 2002
    M.Sc. Computer Science Huazhong University of Science and Technology, China,1994
    B.Sc. Computer Science Huazhong University of Science and Technology, China,1991
















 

























